If a citation requires mapping, the Enterprise Compliance team will have access to a new form called "Manual Attestation Request." This form will be read-only for all other users. Once the request is submitted, a new attestation will be triggered for each affected regional segment within one hour. It cannot be cancelled or updated.

The "Manual Attestation Request" form shall include the following fields:
Date of Request: (Read-only) Automatically populated with the current date and time upon form creation.  This field cannot be modified by the user.
Requested By: (Read-only) Automatically populated with the name of the user submitting the request. This field cannot be modified by the user.
On Behalf Of: (Optional) A free-text field allowing the requester to specify the individual or team they are submitting the request on behalf of.
Brief Description/Justification: (Required) A free-text field where the requester provides a concise explanation for the manual attestation request.  This field is mandatory and must be populated before form submission.
Supporting Documents: (Optional) A file upload field allowing the requester to attach relevant supporting documentation.  Multiple files may be permitted.
